## OpenCode

- Project-level config: `opencode.json`
- oh-my-opencode config: `.opencode/oh-my-opencode.jsonc`
- Project agents/commands/skills/plugins: `.opencode/`
- Operations and verification guide: [docs/OPENCODE.md](docs/OPENCODE.md)
- Quick health check command in OpenCode: `/mcp-health`
- Default addon plugins: `oh-my-opencode`, `opencode-agent-skills`, `superpowers`, `opencode-dynamic-context-pruning`, `opencode-shell-strategy`

### oh-my-opencode

The [oh-my-opencode](https://github.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent) plugin (v3.12+) provides multi-model orchestration with discipline agents:

| Agent | Role | Default Model |
|-------|------|---------------|
| **Sisyphus** | Main ultraworker orchestrator | Claude Opus 4.6 / Kimi K2.5 / GLM-5 |
| **Hephaestus** | Deep autonomous worker (The Legitimate Craftsman) | GPT-5.3 Codex |
| **Prometheus** | Strategic planner (interview mode) | Claude Opus 4.6 |
| **Oracle** | Architecture/debugging advisor | GPT-5.4 |
| **Librarian** | Docs/code search | Gemini 3 Flash |
| **Explore** | Fast codebase grep | Grok Code Fast 1 |

Key commands: `ultrawork` (or `ulw`), `/init-deep`, `/start-work`, `/ralph-loop`

Key features: hash-anchored edits (zero stale-line errors), background agents, LSP/AST tools, skill-embedded MCPs

### Superpowers

The [Superpowers](https://github.com/obra/superpowers) plugin provides composable skills that trigger automatically:

1. **brainstorming** → Socratic design refinement before coding
2. **writing-plans** → Bite-sized tasks with verification steps
3. **subagent-driven-development** → Parallel subagent execution with two-stage review
4. **test-driven-development** → RED-GREEN-REFACTOR enforcement
5. **requesting-code-review** → Pre-review checklist by severity
6. **using-git-worktrees** → Isolated development branches

### opencode-agent-skills

The [opencode-agent-skills](https://github.com/joshuadavidthomas/opencode-agent-skills) plugin provides dynamic skill discovery:
- Auto-discovers skills from `.opencode/skills/`
- Context injection that survives compaction
- Automatic skill matching based on message content

### OpenAgents Control (OAC)

[OpenAgents Control](https://github.com/darrenhinde/OpenAgentsControl) extends OpenCode with pattern-controlled development:
- **ContextScout**: Discovers YOUR coding patterns before generating code
- **Approval gates**: Agents propose → you approve → agents execute
- **3 main agents**: OpenAgent, OpenCoder, SystemBuilder
- **7+ subagents**: ContextScout, TaskManager, CoderAgent, TestEngineer, CodeReviewer, BuildAgent, ExternalScout
- **MVI principle**: 80% token reduction via Minimal Viable Information design
- Commands: `/add-context`, `/commit`, `/test`, `/optimize`
{% if with_gsd %}

### GSD-2 (Get Shit Done)

[GSD v2.28+](https://github.com/gsd-build/GSD-2) (`gsd-pi`) is a standalone autonomous coding agent:

```bash
npm install -g gsd-pi    # Install globally
gsd                       # Start interactive session
# Inside GSD:
/gsd                      # Step mode (one unit at a time)
/gsd auto                 # Autonomous mode — walk away, come back to built software
/gsd status               # Progress dashboard
/gsd discuss              # Architecture discussions alongside auto mode
/gsd quick                # Quick task, skip planning overhead
/gsd keys                 # Manage LLM provider keys
/gsd export --html --all  # Generate HTML milestone reports
```

GSD state lives in `.gsd/` — see `agent-instructions.md` for project-specific context.
Config via `.gsd/preferences.md` — manage interactively with `/gsd prefs`.
Verification commands run automatically after each task (`task lint`, `task test:unit`, `task typecheck`).
